article.headline: Morehead St. 61, W. Illinois 49
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Maze Stallworth scored 14 points as Morehead State beat Western Illinois 61-49 Tuesday night. Stallworth hit a free throw to break a 47-47 tie, then connected on a 3-pointers as the Eagles (1-1) built a 51-47 lead and pulled away for the win. Kenneth Faried added 13 for Morehead, and Leon Buchanan scored 10. David Nurse led the Leathernecks (1-1) with 14 points. Western Illinois led 36-29 with 12:36 left, but Morehead was 10-of-12 from the free throw line in the final 2:28 for the win. The Eagles were 6-of-16 from 3-point range, compared with Western Illinois' 2-of-12 shooting. Morehead also made 17 of 21 free throws, while Western Illinois was 11-of-18.
